 considering setting the truststore to a temporary path and then configuring the system properties. I could use a null value and restore it afterward. Testing a file constructor as a supported configuration seems like a smart move. It should read the RC config and then get the connection, which might lead to more public behavior. Hmm, I'm also wondering if using a temporary file with the driver line would work well.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Testing active class**\\n\\nI need to target the active class, and maybe a good starting point would be to test with an RCData file for parsing. However, it seems that using TempDir might not be necessary for the call, so I should check that. I’m thinking Junit can help with this as I’ll need to write some tests to ensure everything works correctly. Let’s make sure the approach is clear and straightforward!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_2oo5wB3jNIS0cxUlhDptLhXH|fc_058b0007847f2127016a1191201420819db6179263cd4b121f", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.hsqldb/hsqldb/2.4.1/src/test/java/org_hsqldb/hsqldb/RCDataTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_hsqldb.hsqldb;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.sql.Connection;\nimport java.sql.ResultSet;\nimport java.sql.Statement;\n\nimport org.hsqldb.lib.RCData;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Timeout;\n\npublic class RCDataTest {\n    @Test\n    @Timeout(30)\n    void getConnectionLoadsConfiguredJdbcDriverAndOpensConnection() throws Exception {\n        String previousTrustStore = System.getProperty(\"javax.net.ssl.trustStore\");\n        String databaseName = \"rcdata_\" + Long.toUnsignedString(System.nanoTime());\n        String url = \"jdbc:hsqldb:mem:\" + databaseName + \";shutdown=true\";\n        RCData rcData = new RCData(\"memory\", url, \"SA\", \"\", null, null, null, null, null);\n\n        try (Connection connection = rcData.getConnection();\n                Statement statement = connection.createStatement()) {\n            statement.execute(\"CREATE TABLE sample(value INTEGER)\");\n            statement.execute(\"INSERT INTO sample(value) VALUES 42\");\n\n            try (ResultSet resultSet = statement.executeQuery(\"SELECT value FROM sample\")) {\n                assertThat(resultSet.next()).isTrue();\n                assertThat(resultSet.getInt(1)).isEqualTo(42);\n                assertThat(resultSet.next()).isFalse();\n            }\n        } finally {\n            restoreTrustStore(previousTrustStore);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void restoreTrustStore(String previousTrustStore) {\n        if (previousTrustStore == null) {\n            System.clearProperty(\"javax.net.ssl.trustStore\");\n        } else {\n            System.setProperty(\"javax.net.ssl.trustStore\", previousTrustStore);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1544, "output": 1074, "cacheRead": 17408, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 20026, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779536147959, "responseId": "resp_058b0007847f2127016a1191148b50819dbbc283319606ca7b"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_2oo5wB3jNIS0cxUlhDptLhXH|fc_058b0007847f2127016a1191201420819db6179263cd4b121f", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1882 bytes to tests/src/org.hsqldb/hsqldb/2.4.1/src/test/java/org_hsqldb/hsqldb/RCDataTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1779536161077}]}
